data.name: Zschimmer & Schwarz: Paints & Coatings
data.description:
When appearances do matter: technologies and materials from Zschimmer & Schwarz ensure the best results in the treatment and coating of surfaces such as wood, paper, metal, textiles and concrete. Innovative polymer technologies, tailored to the application and requirements of our customers, provide the necessary "plus" in the formulation. As specialists in environmentally conscious, water-based polymers, we offer optimized customer solutions with the highest standards of quality and cost-effectiveness, which we are producing at our sites in Europe, North America and Asia.

Whether it’s raw materials or tailored and ready-to-use customer solutions – we will help you find the right products. We will happily accompany you on the way to your formulation in order to jointly create added value for your customer. For this purpose, please contact our staff via the contact details provided – we look forward to your inquiry!

data.name: SYNTRAN
data.description: SYNTRAN® is a modified-acrylic copolymer with improved flexibility, which is very suitable as a polymer for leather applications and glove coatings. Formulations based on SYNTRAN® for various applications are available upon request.

data.name: SYNPRINT
data.description: SYNPRINT is based on our proprietary self-crosslinking technology. This technology combines two different crosslinking mechanisms on the same polymer backbone, substantially increasing the chemical resistance, water resistance and adhesion to multiple substrates. This technology was designed for the self- crosslinking mechanism to fully cure at room temperature while maintaining long-term shelf stability.

data.name: SYNPRINT AC 9016
data.description:
SYNPRINT AC 9016 is an aqueous self-crosslinking pure acrylic polymer dispersion for use in waterborne coatings, flexographic, screen and gravure inks. Formulations containing SYNPRINT AC 9016 can be adapted to meet the requirements of a wide range of different applications.

Features and Benefits:


	Good adhesion to various substrates
	Very flexible and block resistant
	Very good abrasion resistance
	Resistant to plasticiser migration

data.name: SYNTRAN® PUC 1311
data.description:
SYNTRAN® PUC 1311 is a cationic, semi-rigid PUD with excellent compatibility with inorganic additives and good adhesion to inorganic substrates and functional plastics such as polycarbonate. It also shows good adhesion to cold-rolled sheet. SYNTRAN® PUC 1311 is a self-emulsifying one-component system that shows no migration phenomena because it contains no surfactants.

Features and Benefits:


Good adhesion
High gloss
Excellent water, alkali and weather resistance
Excellent compatibility
Easy film forming at relatively low temperature
Good storage stability with good rheology.
One-component DMAC-based aliphatic polyurethane, low molecular weight, with inorganic additives, good flexibility on cold-rolled sheet

data.name: SYNTRAN® PUC 6225
data.description:
SYNTRAN® PUC 6225 is a cationic, waterborne, one-component, polyester-like, aliphatic polyurethane dispersion with excellent compatibility and good adhesion to metal and inorganic substrates, pigments and functional plastics such as polycarbonate. It has excellent corrosion resistance on cold-rolled sheet metal. It is a self-emulsifying, one-component system that shows no migration characteristics because it contains no surfactants. It is the hard version of SYNTRAN® PUC 6224 and can be used together with cationic acrylates on steel coil. Formulations based on SYNTRAN® PUC 6225 for various applications are available on request.

Features and Benefits:


	Excellent corrosion resistance
	Excellent chemical resistance
	Excellent compatibility/adhesion to pigments and inorganic fillers
	Good adhesion
	High gloss
	Excellent scratch and abrasion resistance
	Good weather resistance

data.name: SYNTRAN® AC 4102
data.description:
SYNTRAN® AC 4102 is a water-based, cationic acrylic copolymer solution. SYNTRAN® AC 4102 is recommended for stain-blocking paints and primers. It shows excellent performance in blocking wood and cork extractives, nicotine, graffiti, soot and water stains. SYNTRAN® AC 4102 is also recommended for the formulation of coatings with excellent adhesion properties on critical substrates, such as glass, ceramic tiles, zinc, aged alkyd paints, etc. SYNTRAN® AC 4102 is recommended for interior use.

Features and Benefits:


	Excellent, universal stain-blocking properties
	Very good blocking of wood extractives
	Very good nicotine barrier properties
	Excellent adhesion to a wide variety of substrates
	Reactive pigments are not required
	Free of APEO and co-solvents

data.name: SYNTRAN® AC 9034
data.description:
SYNTRAN® AC 9034 is a self-crosslinking multiphase acrylic polymer, a multipurpose binder with excellent all-round properties and for coatings with high performance and for less coloring (light color) on "dark oak" substrates.

Features and Benefits:


Excellent early and final water resistance
High hardness
Very good chemical resistance
Resistance against dry heat
Light color on "dark oak"

data.name: SYNTRAN® PUC 9202
data.description:
SYNTRAN® PUC 9202 is a cationic, aqueous polyester-type aliphatic polyurethane dispersion, offering excellent compatibility with and good adhesion to inorganic substrates, pigments, and functional plastics like polycarbonate. SYNTRAN® PUC 9202 is a self-emulsifying one-component system that shows no migration phenomena because it contains no surfactants.

Features and Benefits:


	Good adhesion and high gloss
	Excellent compatibility with inorganic substances
	Excellent resistance to water and alkali and good weather resistance
	Easy film formation at relatively low temperature
	Good storage stability with good rheology
	One-component aliphatic polyurethane, low molecular weight, excellent compatibility with our cationic acrylic emulsions.

data.name: SYNPRINT AC 4110
data.description:
SYNPRINT AC 4110 is a water-based, cationic acrylic copolymer solution. SYNPRINT AC 4110 is recommended for primers with excellent adhesion on critical substrates such as metallised foil. Moreover, films formulated with SYNPRINT AC 4110 form a receptive layer for water-based anionic inks. The low minimum film-forming temperature allows the formulation of low-VOC formulations.

Features and Benefits:


	Excellent adhesion to a wide variety of substrates
	Excellent bonding of anionic inks Low MFFT
	Excellent, universal stain-blocking properties
	Free of APEO and co-solvents

data.name: SYNPRINT AC 6111
data.description: SYNPRINT AC 6111 is a modified water-based acrylic copolymer that combines two different ionic structures in the same interpenetrating polymer network (IPN). This technology allows the formulator to take advantage of a cationic acrylic without the traditional compatibility issues as it can be formulated like a conventional anionic water-based acrylate. This unusual combination provides excellent adhesion to a wide range of difficult substrates. SYNPRINT AC 6111 forms tough flexible films with excellent dry wrinkle behavior.

data.description:

SYNTRAN® AC 4005 is also very suitable for use in stain-blocking paints and primers. It shows excellent performance in blocking wood and cork extractives, nicotine, graffiti, soot and water stains. SYNTRAN® AC 4005 is also recommended for the formulation of coatings with excellent adhesion properties on critical substrates such as glass, ceramic tiles, zinc, aged alkyd paints, etc. SYNTRAN® AC 4005 is recommended for interior use. Various starting point formulations (pigmented and clear) based on SYNTRAN® AC 4005 are available on request.

Features and Benefits:


Excellent, universal stain-blocking properties
Very good blocking of wood extractives
Very good nicotine barrier properties
Excellent adhesion to a wide variety of substrates
Reactive pigments are not required
Free of APEO and co-solvents
Good compatibility with cationic PUDs and some metal salts or other low-pH ingredients for metal passivation.

data.description:
SYNTRAN® AC 5115 is an acrylic polymer based on multiphase technology. This is a proprietary process that combines two different types of polymers in the same polymer network. It allows a balanced combination of the different polymer properties and an overall improvement of the physical properties of both polymers SYNTRAN® AC 5115 forms a film with very high gloss, blocking resistance, rub resistance and printability with various types of inks. It also exhibits excellent adhesion to various substrates.

Features and Benefits:

data.name: SYNTRAN® AC 6045
data.description:
SYNTRAN® AC 6045 is based on a patented interpenetrating network technology with film-forming properties. This technology combining two different ionic structures in the same polymer network increases the adhesion to multiple substrates, wood tannin blocking, stain blocking and dye blocking. This technology allows a formulator to take advantage of the good aspects of a cationic acrylic without the traditional compatibility issues.

Features and Benefits:


	Excellent tannin, stain and dye blocking
	Excellent adhesion to multiple substrates
	High compatibly with other resins and additives
	Quick drying
	Good water resistance
	Outdoor application suitability

data.name: SYNTRAN® AC 6130
data.description:
SYNTRAN AC 6130 is a modified water-based acrylic copolymer that combines two different ionic structures in the same interpenetrating polymer network (IPN). This technology allows the formulator to take advantage of a cationic acrylic without the traditional compatibility issues as it can be formulated like a conventional anionic water-based acrylate. This unusual combination provides excellent adhesion to a wide range of difficult substrates. Coatings formulated with SYNTRAN® AC 6130 consistently exhibit a lasting toughness and flexibility which provide a superior foundation for many of today’s advanced end products.

Features and Benefits:


Excellent solvent resistance and abrasion resistance
Short drying times
High crosslinking density
Improved compatibility
Low solvent demand
Excellent adhesion, hardness and scratch resistance.
Very good water and grease resistance.
Good resistance to coffee and red wine in white coatings, clear when wet, reddish color on wood in clear coatings.

data.name: SYNTRAN® AC 7080
data.description:
SYNTRAN® AC 7080 is an aqueous solution of a polyacrylic acid homopolymer with high molecular weight. SYNTRAN® AC 7080 is free of surfactants upon polymerisation and can remain stable and clear at a low pH (1-3), although the processing temperature should not exceed 110°C. After drying at 20°C and 65% relative humidity, it forms a film that can be used as a smooth protective coating on various surfaces such as synthetic fibers and metals. SYNTRAN® AC 7080 is miscible with water in any ratio and turbidity does not affect the product quality.

Features and Benefits:


	Formation of a clear, hard and tack-free film
	Readily soluble in water
	Protection of metal during its processing (rolling, drawing and cutting, etc.)

data.name: SYNTRAN® DR 7011
data.description:
SYNTRAN® DR 7011 is based on our polymeric surfactant technology. This technology was designed to improve wetting and incorporation of pigments or additives into water-based pigment concentrates and coatings. Used as a grinding resin in pigment dispersions, it improves color development of organic pigments and carbon black. Depending on the application and the objective, SYNTRAN® DR 7011 is typically used in concentrations between 10% and 30%.

Features and Benefits:


	Excellent wetting and dispersibility of pigments
	Highly water sensitive
	High compatibility and stability in multiple formulation types
	Zero VOC requirements to formulate coating.

data.description:
SYNTRAN® WA 1001 is a hard and high melting polyethylene wax emulsion. This wax emulsion is specially designed for OPV, ink and coating applications. It can improve the friction resistance and anti-blocking properties of the surface. SYNTRAN® WA 1001 can be combined with various water-based polymer dispersions.

Features and Benefits:


	Excellent abrasion resistance
	Excellent anti-blocking properties
	Very good compatibility with waterborne base polymers
	Very good water resistance
	Hard and high melting polyethylene wax emulsion.
	Abrasion and scratch resistance, anti-blocking.
	It can improve the friction resistance and anti-blocking properties of the surface

data.name: SYNTRAN® WA 1005
data.description:
SYNTRAN® WA 1005 is a multi-purpose synthetic wax emulsion. It is an ethylene copolymer emulsion of a hard and high melting polyethylene wax specifically designed for use in surface coating applications of different kinds. SYNTRAN® WA 1005 has excellent compatibility and is therefore very well suited for clear wood coatings to improve slip, scratch, abrasion and blocking resistance.

Features and Benefits:


	Very good compatibility with waterborne polymers
	Excellent abrasion resistance
	High slip and anti-blocking
	Very good water resistance.
	Hard and high melting polyethylene wax emulsion.

data.name: Zschimmer & Schwarz: Paints & Coatings
data.description:
When appearances do matter: technologies and materials from Zschimmer & Schwarz ensure the best results in the treatment and coating of surfaces such as wood, paper, metal, textiles and concrete. Innovative polymer technologies, tailored to the application and requirements of our customers, provide the necessary "plus" in the formulation. As specialists in environmentally conscious, water-based polymers, we offer optimized customer solutions with the highest standards of quality and cost-effectiveness, which we are producing at our sites in Europe, North America and Asia.

Whether it’s raw materials or tailored and ready-to-use customer solutions – we will help you find the right products. We will happily accompany you on the way to your formulation in order to jointly create added value for your customer. For this purpose, please contact our staff via the contact details provided – we look forward to your inquiry!
